.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC369AFF9CFFF3FCC5F9F6FB2D261B" blockId="41.[827,1443,1601,1899]" pageId="41" pageNumber="626">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF9CFFF3FCC5F9F6FC652727" box="[827,962,1601,1622]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="626">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
It differs from the other members of 
<taxonomicName id="4C634D19FF9CFFF3FCA3F9D7FC082704" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1879" box="[861,943,1632,1653]" class="Arachnida" family="Cosmetidae" genus="Protus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="41" pageNumber="626" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B917EA88FF9CFFF3FCA3F9D7FC082704" box="[861,943,1632,1653]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="626">Protus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having area 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFF9CFFF3FB77F9D7FB0D2704" box="[1161,1194,1632,1653]" pageId="41" pageNumber="626">III</collectionCode>
armed with larger paramedian yellow tubercles than those of area 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFF9CFFF3FCC5F92AFCF627C3" box="[827,849,1693,1714]" pageId="41" pageNumber="626">II</collectionCode>
(
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFF9CFFF3FC99F92AFC5027C3" box="[871,1015,1693,1715]" captionStart="Figure 31" captionStartId="42.[145,225,1671,1693]" captionTargetBox="[149,757,856,1632]" captionTargetId="figure-329@42.[149,757,856,1632]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="Figure 31. Protus bolivari, male (USNMENT 01538074). A, dorsal view. B, lateral view. C, frontal view. D, panoramic dorsal view. E, ventral view. Scale bars: 1 mm (A–C, E), 2 mm (D)." pageId="41" pageNumber="626">Fig. 31A–C</figureCitation>
), DS with scattered yellow dots in abdomen and carapace (
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFF9CFFF3FB67F90CFAA327A1" box="[1177,1284,1723,1745]" captionStart="Figure 31" captionStartId="42.[145,225,1671,1693]" captionTargetBox="[149,757,856,1632]" captionTargetId="figure-329@42.[149,757,856,1632]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="Figure 31. Protus bolivari, male (USNMENT 01538074). A, dorsal view. B, lateral view. C, frontal view. D, panoramic dorsal view. E, ventral view. Scale bars: 1 mm (A–C, E), 2 mm (D)." pageId="41" pageNumber="626">Fig. 31A</figureCitation>
) and by the combination of the following features: carapace with a thin, yellow stripe bordering anterior margin of carapace (
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFF9CFFF3FC46F8A0FBB9265D" box="[952,1054,1815,1837]" captionStart="Figure 31" captionStartId="42.[145,225,1671,1693]" captionTargetBox="[149,757,856,1632]" captionTargetId="figure-329@42.[149,757,856,1632]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="Figure 31. Protus bolivari, male (USNMENT 01538074). A, dorsal view. B, lateral view. C, frontal view. D, panoramic dorsal view. E, ventral view. Scale bars: 1 mm (A–C, E), 2 mm (D)." pageId="41" pageNumber="626">Fig. 31A</figureCitation>
), 
<collectionCode id="ED72AE5FFF9CFFF3FBC9F8AFFBFD265C" box="[1079,1114,1816,1837]" pageId="41" pageNumber="626">VP</collectionCode>
of the penis not elongated and with distal border substraight (
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFF9CFFF3FB1DF881FAE2263A" box="[1251,1349,1846,1868]" captionStart="Figure 32" captionStartId="43.[163,241,1189,1211]" captionTargetBox="[164,1443,195,1148]" captionTargetId="figure-320@43.[163,1443,195,1149]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="Figure 32. SEM images of some structures of Protus bolivari, male (USNMENT 01538074). A–D, penis: A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, ventral view; D, detail of stylus, oblique view. E–F, right claw IV: E, ventral view; F, ventro-lateral view. Scale bars: 50 μm (A–C), 20 μm (D, F), 100 μm (E)." pageId="41" pageNumber="626">Fig. 32C</figureCitation>
), stylus with short wattle (
<figureCitation id="13582A1FFF9CFFF3FBE9F8E2FBDD261B" box="[1047,1146,1877,1899]" captionStart="Figure 32" captionStartId="43.[163,241,1189,1211]" captionTargetBox="[164,1443,195,1148]" captionTargetId="figure-320@43.[163,1443,195,1149]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="Figure 32. SEM images of some structures of Protus bolivari, male (USNMENT 01538074). A–D, penis: A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, ventral view; D, detail of stylus, oblique view. E–F, right claw IV: E, ventral view; F, ventro-lateral view. Scale bars: 50 μm (A–C), 20 μm (D, F), 100 μm (E)." pageId="41" pageNumber="626">Fig. 32D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
